12/05/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Gjorge Ivanov was officially sworn in Tuesday (May 12th) as Macedonia's new president at a ceremonial session in parliament. In his first address, he pledged to do all he can to improve the quality of life for all citizens. He added, "My political agenda is clear and unambiguous -- Macedonia a member of NATO and the EU, a strong, respected and egalitarian country with proud, rich and happy citizens." Ivanov, who succeeded Branko Crvenkovski, will serve a five-year term. (MIA, Makfax - 12/05/09; Makfax, MIA, MINA - 11/05/09) 
